>>47157089
I usually handwave these depending on the setting
For anthros that evolved over millions of years like us, I usually posit that the differences are milder. How different depends on how intermixed they are with human society and for how long.
For sudden appearances (magic, isekai, reverse isekai, or genetic disaster) it depends on how close they are to the base species. So a world of awoos could have shifted to omnivores as they developed agriculture. Or perhaps garlic is regarded as a highly dangerous drug, a powerful anti-toxin that's only used as a last resort. And then Anon comes along and sprinkles it on everything...

Another consideration is that the poison is in the dose. Indigenous cultures have used potential foodstuffs as drugs since the Stone Age.
Hell, that might be a good point for my Bronze Age story (i'm not smiling)
